The paper deals with the complexity of read-once functions, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of input vectors and the concept of distinguishing functions suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and the use of mathematical proofs, which are common in the sub-categories of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and information theory (cs.IT).
